oor world record was set after the rule came into effect, and thus since it exceeds Bubka's {{T&Fcalc|6.14}} set outdoors, it is also the world record.</ref>\n|[[Sergey Bubka]] \n|{{UKR}}\n|[[Sestriere]], [[Italy]]\n|July 31, 1994<ref name=iaaf/>\n|17\n|-\n|{{T&Fcalc|6.16}} i<ref>{{cite web\n |title       = Progression of IAAF World Records \u2014 2015 edition\n |url         = http://iaaf-ebooks.s3.amazonaws.com/2015/Progression-of-IAAF-World-Records-2015/index.htm\n |publisher   = [[IAAF]]\n |location    = Monte Carlo\n |pages       = 163\u2013171\n |format      = pdf\n |year        = 2015\n |accessdate  = 16 August 2016\n }}</ref>\n|[[Renaud Lavillenie]]\n|{{FRA}}\n|[[Donetsk]], [[Ukraine]]\n|February 15, 2014\n|1\n|-\n|{{T&Fcalc|6.17}} i r\n|[[Armand Duplantis]]\n|{{SWE}}\n|[[Torun]], [[Poland]]\n|February 8, 2020\n|1\n|-\n|{{T&Fcalc|6.18}} i r\n|[[Armand Duplantis]]\n|{{SWE}}\n|[[Glasgow]], [[UK]]\n|February 15, 2020\n|2\n|}\n\n<small>A = mark set at altitude</small>\n<br>\n<small>i = indoor mark</small>\n<br>\n<small>r = pending ratification</small>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Men's pole vault indoor world record progression]]\n* [[Women's pole vault world record progression]]\n* [[Pole vault#Six metres club|List of pole vaulters who reached 6 metres]]\n\n== References ==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://archive.is/20130112231127/http://athletix.org/?p=693 athletix.org data]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20071114184220/http://multimedia.olympic.org/pdf/en_report_92.pdf IOC data]\n* [http://trackandfield.about.com/od/worldrecords/fl/Menrsquos-Pole-Vault-World-Records.htm About]\n\n{{Athletics record progressions}}\n{{Records in athletics}}\n\n[[Category:Men's world athletics record progressions|Pole vault, men]]\n[[Category:Pole vault|World record men]]\n[[Category:World records in athletic jumping|Pole vault, men]]\n[[Category:Men's athletics|World record pole vault]]\n", "name_user": "86.171.10.85", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": 