 from the mouth to its source in the Himalayas.\n* [http://www.sacredland.org/ganges/ An article about the land and the people of the Ganga]\n* [http://www.hydrology.nl/mainnews/1-latest-news/331-the-impacts-of-water-infrastructure-and-climate-change-on-the-hydrology-of-the-upper-ganges-river-basin.html The impacts of water infrastructure and climate change on the hydrology of the Upper Ganga River Basin] IWMI research report\n* [[Bahar Dutt]], {{YouTube|Eqsm5SWORw4|\"Saving the Ganges\"}} [[CNN]]\u2013[[IBN Live]] 5 May 2012.\n* [https://www.npr.org/series/9358334/the-ganges-a-journey-into-india ''The Ganges: A Journey into India'' ([[NPR]])]\n* [https://archive.is/20170828000734/http://www.newindianexpress.com/lifestyle/2016/sep/24/It%E2%80%99s-scientifically-validated-now-Ganga-water-is-%E2%80%98holy%E2%80%99-1524518--1.html It's scientifically validated now; Ganga water is \u2018holy\u2019!]\n\n{{Waters of India}}\n{{Waters of South Asia}}\n{{India Rivers}}\n{{Bangladesh topics}}\n{{Hinduism footer small}}\n{{Hydrography of Uttarakhand}}\n{{Hydrography of Uttar Pradesh}}\n{{Rivers in Bihar}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Ganges| 01]]<!--eponymous cat. 1st-->\n[[Category:Ganges basin|.]]\n[[Category:International rivers of Asia]]\n[[Category:Rivers of Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Rivers of India]]\n[[Category:Bangladesh\u2013India border]]\n[[Category:Border rivers]]\n[[Category:Sacred rivers]]\n[[Category:Rivers of Bihar]]\n[[Category:Rivers of Jharkhand]]\n[[Category:Rivers of Uttarakhand]]\n[[Category:Rivers of Uttar Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Rivers of West Bengal]]\n[[Category:National symbols of India]]\n[[Category:Rigvedic rivers]]\n[[Category:Potamoi]]\n[[Category:Rivers in Buddhism]]\n[[Category:Environmental personhood]]\n", "name_user": "2001:56a:f056:6b00:e531:babc:2be1:dee8", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(The name of the river is either pronounced as Gangaji or Ganga not as Ganges. Their is no word like Ganges in Indian modern or ancient scripture. Kindly change it. Thanks.)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ganges"}
{"title_page": "4KDownload", "text_new": "'''4K Download''' is a range of shareware, [[cross-platform]] programs developed by Open Media LLC, a company based in Nizhny Novgorod, Russia.  All applications run on [[Macintosh|Mac]], [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] and [[Linux]]. 4K Download allows users to download videos and audio from video hosting sites such as [[YouTube]], [[Facebook]] and [[Vimeo]], make a photo backup from [[Instagram]], create and publish slideshows and extract audio from video. The name of the project refers to the name of the video resolution of [[4K resolution|4K]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.addictivetips.com/windows-tips/4k-stogram-lets-you-follow-save-images-of-multiple-instagram-users/|title=4k Stogram Lets You Follow & Save Images Of Multiple Instagram Users|date=2012-07-02|work=AddictiveTips|access-date=2018-07-09|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Programs==\n\n4K Download contains 5 programs:\n* 4K Video Downloader enables download of video, audio, subtitles and playlists from YouTube, Facebook, Vimeo, [[Dailymotion]] and [[Metacafe]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://betanews.com/2012/12/22/4k-video-downloader-claims-to-be-different/|title=4K Video Downloader claims to be different|website=betanews.com|language=en|access-date=2018-07-09}}</ref>\n* 4K Stogram makes backups of Instagram photos on a desktop computer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/261989/download_instagram_photos_in_bulk_with_4k_stogram.html|title=Download Instagram photos in bulk with 4K stogram|work=PCWorld|access-date=2018-07-09|language=en}}</ref>\n*4K YouTube to MP3, which allows videos hosted online from YouTube and select other hosting services to be converted or downloaded to MP3.\n* 4K Slideshow Maker creates and publishes slideshows with Ken Burns effect. It has [[Face detection]] embedded.{{citation needed|date=February 2013}}\n* 4K Video to MP3 converts locally-stored videos into the MP3 audio format.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.abctrick.net/2012/05/4k-video-to-mp3-easily-extract-audio.html|title=4k Video to MP3: Easily Extract Audio From Video Files In MP3 Format For Windows, Mac &amp; Linux|date=2012-07-02|work=ABC Trick - Basic Mobile And Computer Technology|access-date=2018-07-09|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Relations with open source==\nApplications use open source libraries and frameworks: Qt, FFmpeg, boost. Before version 3, it was available as open source software.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sourceforge.net/p/four-k-download/code/ci/default/tree/ |title=4k Download / Code / [b9581e] |accessdate=2014-07-11 |url-status=dead  |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714163427/http://sourceforge.net/p/four-k-download/code/ci/default/tree/ |archivedate=2014-07-14 |df= }}</ref>\n\n==Video Downloader==\n{{Infobox software\n| title = 4K Video Downloader\n| name = 4K Video Downloader\n| screenshot = 4k video downloader.jpg\n| caption =\n| developer = Open Media LLC\n| released = {{Start date and age|2014|05|12|df=yes}}\n| latest release version = 4.11.3.3420\n| latest release date = {{Start date and age|2020|2|04|df=yes}}\n| operating system = [[Microsoft Windows]], [[Mac OS X]], [[Linux]]\n| language = English, German, French, Spanish, Portuguese, Italian, Swedish, Dutch, Hungarian, Finnish, Czech, Polish, Estonian, Russian, Korean, Japanese, Chinese traditional, Chinese simplified.\n| genre = [[Download manager]]\n| license = [[Freemium]], [[Adware]]\n| website = {{url|http://www.4kdownload.com/products/product-videodownloader }}\n}}\n'''4K Video Downloader''' is multi-platform software for downloading video and audio from popular websites [[YouTube]], [[Vimeo]], [[Dailymotion]], [[Facebook]], [[Flickr]], and [[Metacafe]]. It supports the following output formats: [[MP4]], [[Matroska|MKV]], [[OGG Theora]], [[MP3]], [[MPEG-4 Part 14#.MP4_versus_.M4A|M4A]].<ref>{{cite web|url = http://betanews.com/2012/12/22/4k-video-downloader-claims-to-be-different/|title = 4K Video Downloader claims to be different|work = BetaNews|date = 18 August 2012}}</ref> The program allows a user to download channels, playlists, and subtitles, as well as a subscription function, which auto-downloads new videos as they are released on a user-specified YouTube channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.makeuseof.com/tag/4k-video-downloader-makes-it-easy-to-get-videos-from-youtube|title=4K Video Downloader Makes It Easy To Get Videos From YouTube|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cultofmac.com/321650/4k-video-downloader-downloads-videos-simple-sponsored-post/|title=4K Video Downloader makes it easy to grab YouTube videos|date=7 May 2015|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n===Development===\n4K Video Downloader was originally developed in the programming language [[C++]] with [[Qt (software)|QT]] framework using such libraries as [[Boost (C++ libraries)|Boost]], [[FFmpeg]], [[OpenCV]], [[OpenSSL]], [[LAME]], and [[PortAudio]].{{Citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[Comparison of YouTube downloaders]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website}}\n\n{{Download managers}}\n\n[[Category:Free multimedia software]]\n[[Category:Cross-platform software]]\n[[Category:Crowdsourcing]]\n", "text_old": "'''4K Download''' is a range of shareware, [[cross-platform]] programs developed by Open Media LLC, a company based in Nizhny Novgorod, Russia.  All applications run on [[Macintosh|Mac]], [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] and [[Linux]]. 4K Download allows users to download videos and audio from video hosting sites such as [[YouTube]], [[Facebook]] and [[Vimeo]], make a photo backup from [[Instagram]], create and publish slideshows and extract audio from video. The name of the project refers to the name of the video resolution of [[4K resolution|4K]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.addictivetips.com/windows-tips/4k-stogram-lets-you-follow-save-images-of-multiple-instagram-users/|title=4k Stogram Lets You Follow & Save Images Of Multiple Instagram Users|date=2012-07-02|work=AddictiveTips|access-date=2018-07-09|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Programs==\n\n4K Download contains 5 programs:\n* 4K Video Downloader enables download of video, audio, subtitles and playlists from YouTube, Facebook, Vimeo, [[Dailymotion]] and [[Metacafe]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://betanews.com/2012/12/22/4k-video-downloader-claims-to-be-different/|title=4K Video Downloader claims to be different|website=betanews.com|language=en|access-date=2018-07-09}}</ref>\n* 4K Stogram makes backups of Instagram photos on a desktop computer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/261989/download_instagram_photos_in_bulk_with_4k_stogram.html|title=Download Instagram photos in bulk with 4K stogram|work=PCWorld|access-date=2018-07-09|language=en}}</ref>\n*4K YouTube to MP3, which allows videos hosted online from YouTube and select other hosting services to be converted or downloaded to MP3.\n* 4K Slideshow Maker creates and publishes slideshows with Ken Burns effect. It has [[Face detection]] embedded.{{citation needed|date=February 2013}}\n* 4K Video to MP3 converts locally-stored videos into the MP3 audio format.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.abctrick.net/2012/05/4k-video-to-mp3-easily-extract-audio.html|title=4k Video to MP3: Easily Extract Audio From Video Files In MP3 Format For Windows, Mac &amp; Linux|date=2012-07-02|work=ABC Trick - Basic Mobile And Computer Technology|access-date=2018-07-09|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Relations with open source==\nApplications use open source libraries and frameworks: Qt, FFmpeg, boost. Before version 3, it was available as open source software.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sourceforge.net/p/four-k-download/code/ci/default/tree/ |title=4k Download / Code / [b9581e] |accessdate=2014-07-11 |url-status=dead  |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714163427/http://sourceforge.net/p/four-k-download/code/ci/default/tree/ |archivedate=2014-07-14 |df= }}</ref>\n\n==Video Downloader==\n{{Infobox software\n| title = 4K Video Downloader\n| name = 4K Video Downloader\n| screenshot = 4k video downloader.jpg\n| caption =\n| developer = Open Media LLC\n| released = {{Start date and age|2014|05|12|df=yes}}\n| latest release version = 4.11.3.3420\n| latest release date = {{Start date and age|2020|2|04|df=yes}}\n| operating system = [[Microsoft Windows]], [[Mac OS X]], [[Linux]]\n| language = English, German, French, Spanish, Portuguese, Italian, Swedish, Dutch, Hungarian, Finnish, Czech, Polish, Estonian, Russian, Korean, Japanese, Chinese traditional, Chinese simplified.\n| genre = [[Download manager]]\n| license = [[Freemium]], [[Adware]]\n| website = {{url|http://www.4kdownload.com/products/product-videodownloader }}\n}}\n'''4K Video Downloader''' is multi-platform software for downloading video and audio from popular websites [[YouTube]], [[Vimeo]], [[Dailymotion]], [[Facebook]], [[Flickr]], and [[Metacafe]]. It supports the following output formats: [[MP4]], [[Matroska|MKV]], [[OGG Theora]], [[MP3]], [[MPEG-4 Part 14#.MP4_versus_.M4A|M4A]].<ref>{{cite web|url = http://betanews.com/2012/12/22/4k-video-downloader-claims-to-be-different/|title = 4K Video Downloader claims to be different|work = BetaNews|date = 18 August 2012}}</ref> The program allows a user to download channels, playlists, and subtitles, as well as a subscription function, which auto-downloads new videos as they are released on a user-specified YouTube channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.makeuseof.com/tag/4k-video-downloader-makes-it-easy-to-get-videos-from-youtube|title=4K Video Downloader Makes It Easy To Get Videos From YouTube|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cultofmac.com/321650/4k-video-downloader-downloads-videos-simple-sponsored-post/|title=4K Video Downloader makes it easy to grab YouTube videos|date=7 May 2015|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n===Development===\n4K Video Downloader was originally developed in the programming language [[C++]] with [[Qt (software)|QT]] framework using such libraries as [[Boost (C++ libraries)|Boost]], [[FFmpeg]], [[OpenCV]], [[OpenSSL]], [[LAME]], and [[PortAudio]].{{Citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[Comparison of YouTube downloaders]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\nhttps://gen-youtube.shoutmesolution.com\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website}}\n\n{{Download managers}}\n\n[[Category:Free multimedia software]]\n[[Category:Cross-platform software]]\n[[Category:Crowdsourcing]]\n", "name_user": "StevenDoerfler", "label": "safe", "comment": "Deleted random spam URL", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/4KDownload"}
{"title_page": "Bargaon, Odisha", "text_new": "{{more footnotes|date = May 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Bargaon\n| native_name                     = \u092c\u0930\u0917\u093e\u0901 \u0b2c\u0b30\u0b17\u0b3e\u0b01\n| native_name_lang                = \n| other_name                      = Bargaon\n| nickname                        = Baragan\n| settlement_type                 = Village\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| pushpin_map                     = India Odisha#India\n| pushpin_label_position          = right\n| pushpin_map_alt                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Odisha, India\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|20.34|N|82.68|E||display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Odisha]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Nuapada district|Nuapada]]\n| established_title               = <!-- Established -->\n| founder                         = \n| named_for                       = \n| government_type                 = Panchayat\n| governing_body                  = Bargaon Panchayat (1952)\n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = 5\n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = 252\n| population_total                = 2120\n| population_as_of                = 2011\n| population_rank                 = \n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| population_demonym              = \n| population_footnotes            = \n| demographics_type1              = Languages\n| demographics1_title1            = Official\n| demographics1_info1             = [[Oriya language|Odia]], [[Oriya language|Kosli]]\n| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code                     = 766107\n| area_code_type                  = Telephone code\n| area_code                       = 06671\n| registration_plate              = OD-26\n| blank1_name_sec1                = [[Human sex ratio|Sex ratio]]\n| blank1_info_sec1                = 1000:968 [[male]]/[[female]]\n| website                         = {{URL|odisha.gov.in}}\n| footnotes                       = \n| official_name                   = \n| leader_title                    = Sarapanch\n| leader_name                     = Smt. Bimala Majhi\n| leader_title1                   = Samiti Sabhya\n| leader_name1                    = Smt. Pankajini Sabar\n| image_map                       = \n| area_total_ha                   = 505\n| geocode                         = 8MRQ+GX Bargaon, Odisha\n| area_total_acre                 = 1248\n| elevation_ft                    = 827\n}}\n'''Bargaon''' or '''Baragan'''\u00a0is a village under [[Khariar]] Tahasil in\u00a0[[Nuapada district]] of [[Odisha]] state in [[India]]. It is situated 10&nbsp;km away from sub-district headquarter [[Khariar]] and 63&nbsp;km towards south from district headquarter [[Nuapada]]. The word \"Bargaon\" is composed of two words, \"Bara\" means 'Divine' and \"gaan\" means 'village'.  On the 150th birth anniversary of [[Mahatma Gandhi]] , the village was recognised as \"Lok Kala Gram\" of Nuapada district by the Dept. Of Language, Literature and Culture, [[Government of Odisha]]\n\n[[File:GramPanchayat BARGAON.jpg|thumb| GramPanchayat Gate- BARGAON]]\nBARGAON - The Village of History & Culture\n[[File:Maa Chakadongaren Temple.jpg|thumb|Maa Chakadongaren Temple, Bargaon]]\n\n==Economy==\nBargaon is  comes under a rain shadow belt.\nIt has a weekly baazar takes place in every\nTuesday. Most people of Bargaon are middle-\nclass, which includes government\nemployees like Junior Clerks, School Teachers, Forest Guard, Fireman, Odisha Police, OSAP, SOG Army, Small shopkeepers,\nbusinessmen etc.{{fact|date=May 2019}} \n[[File:Weekly_Market_BARGAON.jpg|thumb|Weekly Market on every Tuesday @ BARGAON]]\n'''Bank'''\n[[File:Utkal Grameen Bank.jpg|thumb|Utkal Grameen Bank - BARGAON 192]]\nIn 1984, a branch Kalahandi Anchalik Bank was established in the village for improving the economic standards of people. Nowadays, it is known as Utkal Grameen Bank. \n\n'''Offices'''\n\nThere are some government offices in the village:\n* Post Office\n* Panchayat Office\n[[File:Bargaon Substation.jpg|thumb|33/11KV Electrical Substation, BARGAON]]\n* Electrical Sub-Station\n* Office of the Revenue Inspector\n[[File:Bargaon Indane.jpg|thumb|Bargaon Indane Grameen Vitrak]]\n* BARGAON Indane Grameen Vitrak\n* Primary Agriculture Cooperative Society Office\n\n'''Health Care'''\n\nBasic health care facilities available in the village. \n\n[[File:Maternity & Child Walfare Centre.jpg|thumb|Maternity & Child Walfare Centre, Bargaon]]\n*\n*'''Primary Health Centre (PHC)'''\n*'''Primary Health Sub-centre (PHS)'''\n*'''Maternity and Child Welfare Centre (MCW)'''\n*'''GLOCAL Digital Hospital & Dispensary :'''  <big>It is one of the 241 Digital Dispensaries run\u00a0 across Rajasthan, Bihar, Jharkhand, Odisha, West Bengal, Uttar Pradesh, Chhattisgarh and Manipur. The Digital Dispensary or Digital Hospital aims at providing complete primary and emergency healthcare solution such as consultation from specialist doctors, confirmatory tests, and medicines from a single point.</big>\n*\n*\n\n==Geography==\nBargaon is a village in [[Nuapada district]]. It is located at 20.34\u00b0N 82.68\u00b0E. It has an average elevation of 228m. The village has an area of 505 hectares.\n\nThere are few government and private\nschools in the village. [[Odia language]] is the local language of the people here.\n\n== Places of Interest ==\n\n* '''Chakadongar''' ''':''' \n[[File:Chakadongar.jpg|thumb|Chakadongar - Gateway of BARGAON]]A rounded shaped hills is situated on the eastern part of the village. The NH353 passing through the hill. Maa Chakadongren temple is situated here.\n* '''Teteldongri :'''  Teteldongri and Uddhlu are another hillside situated on the north side of the village. Below the Teteldongri a pond (called parject) is situated and a minor canal is passing nearby. \n* '''Dadhibaman Pokhari :''' A pond is situated on the north east part of the village. The people of Bargaon use it for daily bath. Maa Bandhgosen temple is situated at the centre of the pond.{{fact|date=May 2019}}\n\n==How to Reach ==\nThe village is well connected with roads to many town. National Highway 353 passing near the village which lead to many cities such as [[Raipur]], [[Mahasamund]], \u00a0[[Khariar Road]], [[Nuapada]],  [[Bhawanipatna]], [[Rayagada]] etc.\n\nThe nearest Railway Station is [[Kantabanji]](40&nbsp;km) and nearest Railway Junction is [[Titlagarh]] which is 80&nbsp;km away from Bargaon whereas nearest airport located is at [[Raipur]] (170&nbsp;km) in [[Chhattisgarh]].\n\n==Demographics==\nThe village has around a 5000 population. Average Sex Ratio of Bargaon village is 968 which is lower than Odisha state average of 979. Child Sex Ratio for\nthe Bargaon as per census is 1045, higher than Orissa average of 941. \nBargaon village has lower literacy rate compared to Odisha. In 2011, literacy rate of Bargaon village was 67.41 %\ncompared to 72.87 % of Odisha. In Bargaon Male literacy stands at 79.47 % while female literacy rate was 54.81 %.\n\n==Education==\n\n===Nursery Education===\nThere are several Anganwadi Centre functioning in Bargaon for all round development of the children.\n\n* Anganwadi Centre -1\n* Anganwadi Centre -2\n* Anganwadi Centre -3\n* Anganwadi Centre -4\n*Anganwadi Centre-5\n\n===Primary Education===\n\nPrimary Education play an important role for the development of children in all aspects. However, the primary education have been working in the village since 1918.\n\nBargaon Centre Primary School is one of the oldest school of undivided [[Kalahandi district]].\n\nThe school has celebrated it centenary in the month of December, 2018.\n\n* \n* \n* \n*\n*\n*'''Centre Primary School :''' The school was established in 1918. It is situated at the centre of the village. About 102 batches successfully passed from this school.  [[File:Govt._Primary_School.jpg|thumb|Govt Centre Primary School, Bargaon : School of 100 Years]]\n*\n*'''Sabarpada Project Primary School :''' The school was established in 2002 under the Project of District Primary Education Programme (DPEP), Govt. Of Odisha.\n*'''Kamajori Project Primary School :''' The school was established in 2007 and is managed by Dept. Of School & Mass Education, Govt. Of Odisha.\n*'''Bendrabahal Primary School :''' Bendrabahal Primary School was established in 1966 on the right side of the main road to Bargaon.\n* \n*'''Western Odisha Public School, Bargaon'''\n*'''Bargaon U.P./ M.E. School, Bargaon :''' Bargaon Upper Primary School was established in 1957 is managed by the Dept. Of School and Mass Education, Govt. Of Odisha.  Odia is the medium of instruction in the school. The school has a well building and has a library.  In the year '''2017''' the school was '''merged''' with the '''Jai Kishan High School, Bargaon.'''\n*\n\n===Secondary Education===\n\nFor Secondary Education, there's a Nodal High School namely,\n[[File:Jai Kishan High School.jpg|thumb|Jai Kishan High School, Bargaon]]\n\n*'''Jai Kishan High School, Bargaon'''                  It was established in 1972 by the people of Bargaon. The founder of the school collect some money, land and established the school for the development of local communities and to educate them. Later on the Government of Odisha taken over the responsibility of the school. [[File:Jai Kishan High School Gate.jpg|thumb|Jai Kishan Nodal High School - Gate]]\nNowadays the school is considered as a nodal school in the district. It provides education to both boys and girls from class 6th to class 10th. Both Junior Red Cross (JRC) and Scouts & Guides are functioning in the school.\n*\n*\n*\n*\n\n==Religious Place==\nThere are 4 Shiv temple in the village.\nBesides these there are some Devi mandir also present in the village. Maa Chakadongren, Maa Bandhgosen is worshipped as the Village devi.\n\n==Festivals and rituals==\n[[File:Durga Puja Celebration 2019.jpg|250px|thumb|Durga Puja Celebration 2019]]\n[[File:2019_Durga_Puja_Pendal.jpeg|250px|thumb]]\n\nMany festivals are celebrated in the village. These include:\n\n*'''Durga Puja :''' It is one of the most remarkable major festival or Puja celebrated in the village every year. The festival is observed in the month Ashwina, every year. For the first time, it was starts in the year 1982 and continue celebrated.\n*'''Shivaratri :''' It is one of the another festival celebrated in Bargaon every year. It celebrates in Honor of Lord Shiva. According to the fact, it has been celebrating in the village since 1990.\n*'''Shri Shri Basant Madhumangal Raasleela :''' The most important festival is Raasleela, celebrated every year in the month January or February. It is the festival of Shri Krishna, celebrated for eight days. Some children and some Adults play the role of different characters such as Krishna, Balaram, Madhumangal, Sudam, Subal, King, Dashi, and Shakhi. Kokolila' is the most popular night of Raasleela, it is generally celebrated in the third night of the festival. Since 1889, it was celebrated every year in the village. [[File:Manabasa_Laxmi_Puja_2014.jpg|thumb|Manabasa Laxmi Puja, 2014]]\n\nSome other national and regional festivals are also celebrated in the village. They include Holi, Diwali, Nuakhai, Puspuni, Ganesha Puja, and Gaja Laxmi Puja.{{fact|date=May 2019}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n* Schools in Bargaon : https://schools.org.in/orissa/nuapada/khariar/podapali-p.u.p.s\n* Rain Falls in Bargaon : http://www.fallingrain.com/world/IN/21/Bargaon2.html\n*Postal Information : https://www.postofficeinfo.com/238646/bargaon-post-office-pincode-766107-in-khariar-nuapada-odisha/\n* Sarapanch of Bargaon : https://odishapanchayat.gov.in/English/Pdf/NUAPADA.pdf\n* Bargaon, Census Report 2011 : https://www.census2011.co.in/data/village/421959-bargaon-orissa.html\n\n[[Category:Nuapada district]]\n", "text_old": "{{more footnotes|date = May 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Bargaon\n| native_name                     = \u092c\u0930\u0917\u093e\u0901 \u0b2c\u0b30\u0b17\u0b3e\u0b01\n| native_name_lang                = \n| other_name                      = Bargaon\n| nickname                        = Baragan\n| settlement_type                 = Village\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| pushpin_map                     = India Odisha#India\n| pushpin_label_position          = right\n| pushpin_map_alt                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Odisha, India\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|20.34|N|82.68|E||display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Odisha]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Nuapada district|Nuapada]]\n| established_title               = <!-- Established -->\n| founder                         = \n| named_for                       = \n| government_type                 = Panchayat\n| governing_body                  = Bargaon Panchayat (1952)\n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| area_