'village'.  On the 150th birth anniversary of [[Mahatma Gandhi]] , the village was recognised as \"Lok Kala Gram\" of Nuapada district by the Dept. Of Language, Literature and Culture, [[Government of Odisha]]\n\n[[File:GramPanchayat BARGAON.jpg|thumb| GramPanchayat Gate- BARGAON]]\nBARGAON - The Village of History & Culture\n[[File:Maa Chakadongaren Temple.jpg|thumb|Maa Chakadongaren Temple, Bargaon]]\n\n==Economy==\nBargaon is  comes under a rain shadow belt.\nIt has a weekly baazar takes place in every\nTuesday. Most people of Bargaon are middle-\nclass, which includes government\nemployees like Junior Clerks, School Teachers, Forest Guard, Fireman, Odisha Police, OSAP, SOG Army, Small shopkeepers,\nbusinessmen etc.{{fact|date=May 2019}} \n[[File:Weekly_Market_BARGAON.jpg|thumb|Weekly Market on every Tuesday @ BARGAON]]\n'''Bank'''\n[[File:Utkal Grameen Bank.jpg|thumb|Utkal Grameen Bank - BARGAON 192]]\nIn 1984, a branch Kalahandi Anchalik Bank was established in the village for improving the economic standards of people. Nowadays, it is known as Utkal Grameen Bank. \n\n'''Offices'''\n\nThere are some government offices in the village:\n* Post Office\n* Panchayat Office\n[[File:Bargaon Substation.jpg|thumb|33/11KV Electrical Substation, BARGAON]]\n* Electrical Sub-Station\n* Office of the Revenue Inspector\n[[File:Bargaon Indane.jpg|thumb|Bargaon Indane Grameen Vitrak]]\n* BARGAON Indane Grameen Vitrak\n* Primary Agriculture Cooperative Society Office\n\n'''Health Care'''\n\nBasic health care facilities available in the village. \n\n[[File:Maternity & Child Walfare Centre.jpg|thumb|Maternity & Child Walfare Centre, Bargaon]]\n*\n*Primary Health Centre (PHC)\n*Primary Health Sub-centre (PHS)\n*'''<big><u>GLOCAL Digital Dispensary or Hospital</u>  <u>:</u></big>'''   <big>It is one of the 241 Digital Dispensaries run\u00a0 across Rajasthan, Bihar, Jharkhand, Odisha, West Bengal, Uttar Pradesh, Chhattisgarh and Manipur. Litmus MX, Litmus DX and Litmus RX are the three major components of this digital Dispensary. The Digital Dispensary or Digital Hospital aims at providing complete primary and emergency healthcare solution such as consultation from specialist doctors, confirmatory tests, and medicines from a single point.</big> \n*\n*Maternity and Child Welfare Centre (MCW)\n\n==Geography==\nBargaon is a village in [[Nuapada district]]. It is located at 20.34\u00b0N 82.68\u00b0E. It has an average elevation of 228m. The village has an area of 505 hectares.\n\nThere are few government and private\nschools in the village. [[Odia language]] is the local language of the people here.\n\n== Places of Interest ==\n\n* '''Chakadongar''' ''':''' \n[[File:Chakadongar.jpg|thumb|Chakadongar - Gateway of BARGAON]]A rounded shaped hills is situated on the eastern part of the village. The NH353 passing through the hill. Maa Chakadongren temple is situated here.\n* '''Teteldongri :'''  Teteldongri and Uddhlu are another hillside situated on the north side of the village. Below the Teteldongri a pond (called parject) is situated and a minor canal is passing nearby. \n* '''Dadhibaman Pokhari :''' A pond is situated on the north east part of the village. The people of Bargaon use it for daily bath. Maa Bandhgosen temple is situated at the centre of the pond.{{fact|date=May 2019}}\n\n==How to Reach ==\nThe village is well connected with roads to many town. National Highway 353 passing near the village which lead to many cities such as [[Raipur]], [[Mahasamund]], \u00a0[[Khariar Road]], [[Nuapada]],  [[Bhawanipatna]], [[Rayagada]] etc.\n\nThe nearest Railway Station is [[Kantabanji]](40&nbsp;km) and nearest Railway Junction is [[Titlagarh]] which is 80&nbsp;km away from Bargaon whereas nearest airport located is at [[Raipur]] (170&nbsp;km) in [[Chhattisgarh]].\n\n==Demographics==\nThe village has around a 5000 population. Average Sex Ratio of Bargaon village is 968 which is lower than Odisha state average of 979. Child Sex Ratio for\nthe Bargaon as per census is 1045, higher than Orissa average of 941. \nBargaon village has lower literacy rate compared to Odisha. In 2011, literacy rate of Bargaon village was 67.41 %\ncompared to 72.87 % of Odisha. In Bargaon Male literacy stands at 79.47 % while female literacy rate was 54.81 %.\n\n==Education==\n\n===Nursery Education===\nThere are several Anganwadi Centre functioning in Bargaon for all round development of the children.\n\n* Anganwadi Centre -1\n* Anganwadi Centre -2\n* Anganwadi Centre -3\n* Anganwadi Centre -4\n*Anganwadi Centre-5\n\n===Primary Education===\n\nPrimary Education play an important role for the development of children in all aspects. However, the primary education have been working in the village since 1918.\n\nBargaon Centre Primary School is one of the oldest school of undivided [[Kalahandi district]].\n\nThe school has celebrated it centenary in the month of December, 2018.\n\n* \n* \n* \n*\n*\n*'''Centre Primary School :''' The school was established in 1918. It is situated at the centre of the village. About 102 batches successfully passed from this school.  [[File:Govt._Primary_School.jpg|thumb|Govt Centre Primary School, Bargaon : School of 100 Years]]\n*\n*'''Sabarpada Project Primary School :''' The school was established in 2002 under the Project of District Primary Education Programme (DPEP), Govt. Of Odisha.\n*'''Kamajori Project Primary School :''' The school was established in 2007 and is managed by Dept. Of School & Mass Education, Govt. Of Odisha.\n*'''Bendrabahal Primary School :''' Bendrabahal Primary School was established in 1966 on the right side of the main road to Bargaon.\n* \n*'''Western Odisha Public School, Bargaon'''\n*'''Bargaon U.P./ M.E. School, Bargaon :''' Bargaon Upper Primary School was established in 1957 is managed by the Dept. Of School and Mass Education, Govt. Of Odisha.  Odia is the medium of instruction in the school. The school has a well building and has a library.  In the year '''2017''' the school was '''merged''' with the '''Jai Kishan High School, Bargaon.'''\n*\n\n===Secondary Education===\n\nFor Secondary Education, there's a Nodal High School namely,\n[[File:Jai Kishan High School.jpg|thumb|Jai Kishan High School, Bargaon]]\n\n*'''Jai Kishan High School, Bargaon'''                  It was established in 1972 by the people of Bargaon. The founder of the school collect some money, land and established the school for the development of local communities and to educate them. Later on the Government of Odisha taken over the responsibility of the school. [[File:Jai Kishan High School Gate.jpg|thumb|Jai Kishan Nodal High School - Gate]]\nNowadays the school is considered as a nodal school in the district. It provides education to both boys and girls from class 6th to class 10th. Both Junior Red Cross (JRC) and Scouts & Guides are functioning in the school.\n*\n*\n*\n*\n\n==Religious Place==\nThere are 4 Shiv temple in the village.\nBesides these there are some Devi mandir also present in the village. Maa Chakadongren, Maa Bandhgosen is worshipped as the Village devi.\n\n==Festivals and rituals==\n[[File:Durga Puja Celebration 2019.jpg|250px|thumb|Durga Puja Celebration 2019]]\n[[File:2019_Durga_Puja_Pendal.jpeg|250px|thumb]]\n\nMany festivals are celebrated in the village. These include:\n\n*'''Durga Puja :''' It is one of the most remarkable major festival or Puja celebrated in the village every year. The festival is observed in the month Ashwina, every year. For the first time, it was starts in the year 1982 and continue celebrated.\n*'''Shivaratri :''' It is one of the another festival celebrated in Bargaon every year. It celebrates in Honor of Lord Shiva. According to the fact, it has been celebrating in the village since 1990.\n*'''Shri Shri Basant Madhumangal Raasleela :''' The most important festival is Raasleela, celebrated every year in the month January or February. It is the festival of Shri Krishna, celebrated for eight days. Some children and some Adults play the role of different characters such as Krishna, Balaram, Madhumangal, Sudam, Subal, King, Dashi, and Shakhi. Kokolila' is the most popular night of Raasleela, it is generally celebrated in the third night of the festival. Since 1889, it was celebrated every year in the village. [[File:Manabasa_Laxmi_Puja_2014.jpg|thumb|Manabasa Laxmi Puja, 2014]]\n\nSome other national and regional festivals are also celebrated in the village. They include Holi, Diwali, Nuakhai, Puspuni, Ganesha Puja, and Gaja Laxmi Puja.{{fact|date=May 2019}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n* Schools in Bargaon : https://schools.org.in/orissa/nuapada/khariar/podapali-p.u.p.s\n* Rain Falls in Bargaon : http://www.fallingrain.com/world/IN/21/Bargaon2.html\n*Postal Information : https://www.postofficeinfo.com/238646/bargaon-post-office-pincode-766107-in-khariar-nuapada-odisha/\n* Sarapanch of Bargaon : https://odishapanchayat.gov.in/English/Pdf/NUAPADA.pdf\n* Bargaon, Census Report 2011 : https://www.census2011.co.in/data/village/421959-bargaon-orissa.html\n\n[[Category:Nuapada district]]\n", "name_user": "DK6771", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bargaon,_Odisha"}
{"title_page": "Love-stricken", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2014}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Love-stricken (\n| image = Delshodegan.jpg\n| image_size = \n| alt = \n| caption = International poster\n| director = [[Ali Hatami]]\n| producer = Ali Hatami\n| writer = Ali Hatami\n| starring = [[Mohammad Ali Keshavarz]]<br />[[Akbar Abdi]]<br />[[Amin Tarokh]]<br />[[Saeed Poorsamimi]]<br />Faramarz Sedighi<br />Fathali Oveisi <br /> [[Leila Hatami]]\n| music = [[Hossein Alizadeh]]\t\n| cinematography = [[Mahmoud Kalari]]\n| editing = Ruhollah Emami\n| distributor = \n| released = 1992\n| runtime = 91 minutes\n| country = [[Iran]]\n| language = Persian\n| budget = \n| gross =\n}}\n'''Love-stricken''' (in [[Persian language|Persian]]:''\u062f\u0644\u200c\u0634\u062f\u06af\u0627\u0646'';) is a 1992 [[Iranian cinema|Iranian]] [[historical drama]] film directed by [[Ali Hatami]]. The movie is mainly about some [[Iranian traditional music|Iranian]] classical musicians in [[Qajar dynasty|Ghajar era]] and their struggle to release their first Record which takes them on a journey to France. The film uses many notable Iranian actors and actresses. Among them are: [[Amin Tarokh]], [[Akbar Abdi]], [[Saeed Poorsamimi|Saeed Poursamimi]], [[Mohamad Ali Keshavarz]], [[Jamshid Hashempur|Jamshid Hashempour]], [[Hamid Jebelli]], [[Fathali Oveisi]], [[Shahla Riahi]], [[Leili Rashidi]], [[Leila Hatami]],and [[Anna Borkowska (actress)|Anna Borkowska]].\n\nLove-stricken is in celebration and praise of [[Iranian music]]. At the beginning of the film an [[intertitle]] is seen which says: \"This film is dedicated to The Great Masters of Iranian Music in the millennium anniversary of [[Barbad]]\". The film music was composed by famous Iranian musicians such as [[Hossein Aliz\u00e2deh|Hussein Alizadeh]] as composer and [[Mohammad Reza Shajarian]] as singer. Love-stricken was 13th film of Ali Hatami after some both commercial and artistic successes of his previous films like: [[Mother (1991 film)|Mother]], [[Sooteh-Delan]], [[Sattar Khan (film)|Sattar Khan]], [[Hajji Washington (film)|Hajji Washington]] and [[Kamalolmolk (film)|Kamalolmolk]].\n\n== Title ==\nAccording to [[Dehkhoda]] [[Dehkhoda Dictionary|dictionary]], the word \"Del Shodegan\" is the [[plural]] form of \"Delshodeh\". In [[Persian language|Persian]] it means \"the lovelorn\" or \"worried\" people. \"love-stricken\" or \"love-struck\" is another translation.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u062f\u0644\u0634\u062f\u06af\u0627\u0646{{!}} \u0644\u063a\u062a\u0646\u0627\u0645\u0647 \u062f\u0647\u062e\u062f\u0627|url=http://www.loghatnaameh.org/dehkhodaworddetail-bf9b61b90f3b4d1a9436f3ad787b9934-fa.html|publisher=[[Dehkhoda dictionary]]|access-date=11 May 2014|archive-url=https://archive.is/20140511211644/http://www.loghatnaameh.org/dehkhodaworddetail-bf9b61b90f3b4d1a9436f3ad787b9934-fa.html|archive-date=11 May 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\n\nHis imperial majesty [[Ahmad Shah Qajar]] asks a group of Iranian musicians, unaffiliated with the royal court, to record a sample of [[Iranian classical music|Persian Classical Music]] on newly invented [[gramophone record|gramophone]] at the [[Conservatoire de Paris]]. A group of best musicians gather under the direction of [[Ostad|Maestro]] Delnavaz. A singer named Taher (Amin Tarokh) also accompanies them to the journey to Paris.\n\nThey can record several [[gramophone disc]]s after a lot of troubles. Taher who has fallen in love with a blind Turkish princess dies of an illness. As the others decide to come back to [[Iran]], one of them says he wants to stay in Europe and learn \"scientific music\". Other members return to Iran with broken hearts, their friend's corpse and some recorded gramophone discs of Iranian treasure.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n*Faramarz Sadighi as Maestro Delnavaz\n*[[Amin Tarokh]] as Taher Khan Bahr-eh Nour\n*[[Akbar Abdi]] as Agha Faraj Boulsik\n*[[Jamshid Hashempur]] as Iran's Ambassador to France\n*[[Shahla Riahi]] as Delnavaz's Wife\n*[[Saeed Poorsamimi|Saeed Poursamimi]] as Naser-Khan Deylaman\n*[[Mohamad Ali Keshavarz]] as Mirza Mahmoud\n*[[Hamid Jebelli|Hamid Jebeli]] as Khosro Khan Rahabi\n*[[Leila Hatami]] as Leila\n*[[Leili Rashidi]] as Agha Faraj's Wife\n*[[Anna Borkowska (actress)|Anna Borkowska]] as Madam\n*Saeed Amir Soleymani as Nayeb Al-saltaneh\n*Jalal Moghadam as Eesa-khan-e Vazir\n*Rogheyeh Chehreh-Azad as Dayeh\n*Turan Mehrzad as Naser Khan's Wife\n*[[Mehri Vadadian]] as Faraj's Mother\n*Soroor Nejatollahi as Khosor Khan's Wife\n*Hooshang Beheshti as Haj Agha Monfared Nabatriz\n*Ali Asghar Garmsiri as Ostad Yousef\n*Babak Eskandari as [[Ahmad Shah Qajar|Ahmad Shah]]\n*Elmira Abdi as Agha Faraj Daughter\n*Foad Chavmeh as Taher's Childhood\n*Rashid Aslani as Afandi\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Production==\nAli Hatami wrote about 4 hours of [[Screenplay|script]] for Love-stricken. Although all of the script was shot, but they had to edit it to a normal 90 minutes film. the actual film was shot in 19 acts, but Hatami cut out about 10 acts of it in the editing room.<ref>{{cite web|last=Anari|first=Ali|title=\u0646\u0627\u0634\u0646\u06cc\u062f\u0647\u200c\u0647\u0627\u06cc\u06cc \u0627\u0632 \u0639\u0644\u06cc \u062d\u0627\u062a\u0645\u06cc\u060c \u0645\u0631\u062f \u0647\u0632\u0627\u0631 \u062f\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646 \u0633\u06cc\u0646\u0645\u0627\u06cc \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646|url=http://khabaronline.ir/detail/113716/|publisher=Khabar Online}}</ref>\n\n==Music==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Love-stricken <br /> <small>(Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)</small>\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Hossein Alizadeh]] and [[Mohammad Reza Shajarian]]\n| cover      = Delshodegan music.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = 2000\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      =\n| length     = 56:13\n| label      =\n| producer   =\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\nMusic of the film is composed by Hossein Alizadeh ([[tar]]), [[Saeed Farajpouri]] ([[kamancheh]]), [[Arshad Tahmasebi]] (tar) and [[Dariush Zargari]] ([[santur]]). [[Mohammad Reza Shajarian]] is the lead singer of the score.<ref>{{cite web|title=Delshodeghan by M. R. SHAJARIAN & Hossein ALIZADEH|url=http://www.cdbaby.com/cd/shajaraliza|publisher=[[cdbaby]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\u0622\u0644\u0628\u0648\u0645 \u0645\u0648\u0633\u06cc\u0642\u06cc \u0645\u062a\u0646 \u0641\u06cc\u0644\u0645 \u062f\u0644\u0634\u062f\u06af\u0627\u0646|url=http://old.leila-hatami.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=773:-lr&catid=51:gallery}}</ref> Although at first Hatami wanted [[Hossein Dehlavi]] to cooperate with Alizadeh but Dehlavi thought it would be better if Alizadeh worked on the tracks alne.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u062a\u062c\u0631\u0628\u0647 \u062f\u0644\u0634\u062f\u06af\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0632 \u0632\u0628\u0627\u0646 \u062d\u0633\u06cc\u0646 \u0639\u0644\u06cc\u0632\u0627\u062f\u0647|url=http://fararu.com/fa/news/174447/%D8%AA%D8%AC%D8%B1%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%AF%D9%84%D8%B4%D8%AF%DA%AF%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%B2%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%AD%D8%B3%DB%8C%D9%86-%D8%B9%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%87|publisher=Fararu.com}}</ref> For the lyrics different poems of [[Hafiz Shirazi|Hafiz]], [[Fereydun Moshiri]] and Ali Hatami was used.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u062f\u0644\u0634\u062f\u06af\u0627\u0646|url=http://musicaneh.ir/album/3345688-%D8%AF%D9%84%D8%B4%D8%AF%DA%AF%D8%A7%D9%86|publisher=\u0645\u0648\u0632\u06cc\u06a9\u0627\u0646\u0647}}</ref> \n\u0670The soundtrack is dedicated to The Great Masters of Iranian Music in the millennium anniversary of [[Barbad]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Album cover of Delshodegan|url=http://dl.leila-hatami.com/files/audio/delshodegan/delshodegan02.jpg}}</ref>\n\n=== Track listing===\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed       = \n| headline        = \n| extra_column    = Artist(s)\n\n| title1          = Tar-o-Pud\n| extra1          = Hossein Alizadeh\n| length1